The RV85 is a fine piece of wood and steel. CZ did a fantastic job building these as the hardwood stocks and blued steel are absolutely beautiful. The canvas and leather are equally as nice. This is a great collectors item and conversation piece.

Each rifle comes like new in box (original packaging) with a complete set of accessories including: 1) Cleaning kit 2) Original Test Target 3)Maintenance tools 4) Manual 5) Log book (with stamps and signatures from originating test fire, assembly, and packing employees) 6) Leather Sling 7) Canvas Carry Case 8)Spare springs and firing pin. title: For Sale:  RARE Proto-Type R.H. Ruana Knife and Sheath
postcontent:
Original "Rudy" RUANA Prototype Hunting knife and Sheath
This is one of the first knives that RUDY RUANA ever made when he started the business of RUANA KNIFE WORKS!
This knife was taken to RUANA KNIFE WORKS Inc. and inspected 2 times by President Victor N. Hangas. Victor did state and included it in his stamped letter on business letterhead that this knife and sheath was in fact made by Rudy Ruana between the dates of 1938 and 1944. It was made before Rudy stamped his knives with the Ruana logo. The blade being cast alluminum, handle with cut Elk antlers and the handle of cast Alluminum. The blade being of Hardened steal car springs, what Rudy used when starting his Knife business. 
The sheath also being originally made at the time of the knife. The strap having a buckle instead of the common snap found on modern knife sheaths. Victor Hangas also saying the Pins used to hold the leather sheath together have not been used in decades, now using rivets. 
Also included with the knife and the LOA from RUANA KNIFE WORKS Inc. is a letter from deceased Ed Swanson who grew up with Rudy Ruana in Bonner, Montana. The letter written in 2002 stating that Ed's father bought the knife from Rudy when Rudy began the factory. Ed's father using the knife for hunting mid century and when Ed's father passed away, Ed receiving the knife. Ed then passed this knife along to a close family friend John Hinckley, who I am assisting in the sale of this knife. 
HOW OFTEN DO YOU FIND A PIECE OF HISTORY WITH FULL DOCUMENTATION OF ITS HISTORY recorded and documented by the decendent and president of the company Victor Hangas and original owner Ed Swanson? Last week, (last week of November 2011), Knife owner John Hinckley went and again spoke with Victor Hangas about the knife and getting a legitimate estimate of its true value. Victor Hangas gave a solid estimate of the area of $5000.00 because of the rarity of the knife, also because it is one of the first prototypes to what is now RUANA KNIFE WORKS Inc. Hangas said any winning bidder is free to contact him directly with any questions of the value or about the knife and sheath. 
FEEL Free to ask questions but SERIOUS inquiries only

AUCTION ONLY VALID IN THE USA! 


all sales are final
